Module mesakit.graph.core
Package com.telenav.mesakit.graph.metadata

Class DataSpecification

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.mesakit.graph.metadata.DataSpecification
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
CommonDataSpecification
public abstract class DataSpecification extends Object implements com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject
A specification of Graph data and its storage, independent of format or supplier. For example, data of UniDB origin can come from HERE or TomTom suppliers and it could be in PBF or CSV format (or it could have no format, coming directly from UniDB by query). See DataFormat, DataSupplier and Metadata for details.

The set of Attributes that are supported by a data specification can be queried with supports(Attribute) and attributes(). The attributes supported by individual classes of GraphElements can be discovered with edgeAttributes(), vertexAttributes(), relationAttributes() and placeAttributes(). Note that all of these methods have convenience methods in Graph, so there's no need to directly query the graph's DataSpecification.

The factory methods of a data specification are used to create graphs and graph elements, as specified by a subclass. enabling specialization. It is not allowable to create Graph objects directly.. This restriction is is enforced by a stack check in the Graph constructor, ensuring that all graphs are created and initialized according to a data specification.

The abstract CommonDataSpecification specifies default graph, graph store and graph element implementations which implement attributes that are common to both OSM and UniDb. Additional attributes and functionality are added by the OsmDataSpecification.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
